ows%20how%20the%20economy%20has%20looked%20in%20the%20first%20three%20months%20of%20Trump's%20second%20term.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20real%20gross%20domestic%20product%20fell%20at%20an%20annualized%20rate%20of%200.3%25%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20contraction%20was%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202022%2C%20which%20triggered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-gdp-q1-economic-growth-inflation-omicron-wave-coronavirus-recovery-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efears%20of%20a%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20didn't%20materialize.%20It's%20also%20far%20below%20the%20growth%20rate%20of%202.4%25%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20decrease%20in%20real%20GDP%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20primarily%20reflected%20an%20increase%20in%20imports%2C%20which%20are%20a%20subtraction%20in%20the%20calculation%20of%20GDP%2C%20and%20a%20decrease%20in%20government%20spending%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%20news%20release%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20movements%20were%20partly%20offset%20by%20increases%20in%20investment%2C%20consumer%20spending%2C%20and%20exports.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FSwE6Z%2F4%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Change%20in%20real%20GDP%20from%20previous%20quarter%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22479%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20report%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%20showed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-economy-stagflation-recession-high-inflation-unemployment-stock-market-crash-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20the%20economy%20has%20performed%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20first%20three%20months%20of%20President%20Donald%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-100th-day-inflation-economy-tariffs-markets-stocks-businesses-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20second%20presidency%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Since%20the%20inauguration%2C%20the%20administration%20has%20made%20cuts%20to%20the%20federal%20government%20and%20announced%20tariffs%2C%20including%20on%20key%20trade%20partners%20like%20China%20and%20automobiles%20and%20some%20automobile%20parts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnytime%20you%20see%20a%20contraction%2C%20or%20the%20opposite%20of%20economic%20growth%2C%20it%20is%20a%20concern%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Hamrick%2C%20a%20senior%20economic%20analyst%20at%20Bankrate%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20before%20the%20GDP%20release.%20%26quot%3BBut%20ultimately%20the%20question%20also%20is%20about%20the%20outlook.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamrick%20added%20there%20are%20global%20headwinds%20to%20the%20US%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20tariffs%20and%20trade.%20%26quot%3BTariffs%20present%20an%20upside%20risk%20to%20inflation%20and%20a%20downside%20risk%20to%20employment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20spending%20fell%20at%20a%20seasonally%20adjusted%20annual%20rate%20of%205.1%25%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20report%20provides%20insight%20into%20how%20businesses%20prepared%20for%20tariffs.%20While%20imports%20increased%2041.3%25%2C%20exports%20increased%201.8%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPersonal%20consumption%20expenditures%20also%20increased%201.8%25%2C%20a%20smaller%20gain%20than%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202024.%20Gross%20private%20domestic%20investment%20climbed%2021.9%25%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20with%20fixed%20investment%20in%20equipment%20surging%2022.5%25%20after%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStock%20futures%20were%20down%20after%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20softer%20Q1%20GDP%20figures%20were%20likely%20significantly%20skewed%20to%20the%20downside%20by%20the%20record%20widening%20of%20the%20U.S.%20trade%20deficit%2C%20the%20economic%20outlook%20remains%20pessimistic%20and%20uncertain%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20Weldon%2C%20investment%20director%20and%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20IFM%20Investors%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeldon%20added%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bnegative%20impacts%20of%20the%20current%20tariff%20policy%20will%20only%20compound%20every%20day%20there%20are%20no%20resolutions%2C%20as%20imports%20stagnate%20on%20tepid%20demand%20and%20small%20and%20medium%20businesses%20are%20forced%20to%20make%20tough%20decisions%20on%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20hard%20data%20measures%20haven't%20reflected%20policy%20changes%20just%20yet.%20Still%2C%20the%20back%20and%20forth%20on%20tariff%20announcements%20and%20suspensions%20have%20contributed%20to%20people%20feeling%20worried%20or%20like%20they%20must%20spring%20into%20action%2C%20which%20has%20been%20reflected%20in%20some%20recent%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-consumers-buying-cars-retail-sales-price-increases-inventory-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretail%20sales%3C%2Fa%3E%20increased%20at%20motor%20vehicles%20and%20parts%20dealers.%20Consumers%20could%20face%20higher%20prices%20there%20and%20other%20areas%20of%20the%20economy%20as%20dealerships%20and%20business%20owners%20make%20tariff-related%20decisions.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-march-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20continued%20to%20slow%20down%2C%20but%20people%20are%20worried%20that%20it%20could%20accelerate%20because%20of%20tariffs.%20Hamrick%20said%20the%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3Beconomy%20is%20being%20affected%20by%20both%20the%20perceived%20and%20anticipated%20impacts%20of%20tariffs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Kelly%2C%20chief%20global%20strategist%20at%20J.P.%20Morgan%20Asset%20Management%2C%20said%20in%20a%20note%20before%20the%20GDP%20release%20that%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20a%20quick%20resolution%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-increase-prices-empty-shelves-timeline-supply-chain-holidays-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20imports%2C%20exports%20and%20inventories%20all%20look%20set%20to%20fall%20sharply.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20people%20may%20slow%20down%20on%20making%20purchases%2C%20and%20companies%20may%20make%20some%20business%20changes%20like%20scaling%20back%20on%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFurther%20federal%20cutbacks%20should%20prevent%20an%20overall%20government%20spending%20bounce-back%2C%20while%20tourism%20will%20likely%20be%20hit%20by%20the%20international%20reaction%20to%20the%20Administration's%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20said.%20%26quot%3BGiven%20all%20of%20this%2C%20real%20GDP%20growth%20could%20be%20very%20slow%2C%20or%20even%20negative%2C%20over%20at%20least%20the%20first%20three%20quarters%20of%202025.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWednesday's%20release%20reflects%20an%20advance%20estimate%2C%20so%20there's%20a%20chance%20real%20GDP%20could%20be%20revised%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%20While%20the%20new%20GDP%20report%20doesn't%20mean%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-prediction-us-economy-downturn-trump-tariffs-inflation-wealth-2025-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecession%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20are%20concerns%20about%20how%20the%20economy%20will%20evolve.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20huge%20wildcard%20in%20the%20face%20of%20a%20high%20degree%20of%20uncertainty%20felt%20by%20consumers%20and%20business%20leaders%20all%20of%20which%20undermines%20their%20ability%20to%20make%20decisions%20including%20on%20spending%20which%20would%20lend%20support%20to%20the%20economy%2